value: Breeds in northern Europe and western Asia from northern Norway, southern Finland, the White Sea and the Ibwer Yenessei, south to Den- mark, East Prussia, Poland, Bessarabia, Kirghiz Steppes and the Altai. Migrates through southern Europe and southwestern Asia; winters in Africa, south of the Sahara, mainly in the east.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Palearctic winter visitor, marshland, flooded areas but drier parts than Common Snipe: all S of Sahara except NE and SW.
Breeds n Palearctic region; winters in sub-Saharan Africa
lake edges, seasonally flooded areas, esp in short sedge, short grass
